obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (26950)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the State of Himachal Pradesh Act, 1970.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26950&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (26951)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26951&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the administrator appointed by the President under article 239 of the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(b) "appointed day" means the day which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(c) "article" means an article of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(d) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission appointed by the President under`
  line `article 324;`
  line
  line `(e) "existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh" means the Union territory of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh as existing immediately before the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(f) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme, notification`
  line `or other instrument having, immediately before the appointed day, the force of law in the whole or`
  line `any part of the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(g) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, means a person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is a member of that House or that Assembly;`
  line
  line `(h) "treasury" includes a sub-treasury.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (26952)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of State of Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26952&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `established a new State, to be known as the State of Himachal Pradesh, comprising the territories which`
  line `immediately before that day were comprised in the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (26953)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26953&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution,`
  line
  line `(a) under the heading "I. THE STATES," after entry 17, the following entry shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `"18. Himachal Pradesh The territories which immediately before`
  line `the commencement of this Constitution`
  line `were being administered as if they were`
  line `Chief Commissioners' Provinces under the`
  line `names of Himachal Pradesh and Bilaspur`
  line `and the territories specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Punjab`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1966.";`
  line
  line `(b) under the heading "II. THE UNION TERRITORIES", entry 2 relating to Himachal Pradesh`
  line `shall be omitted and entries 3 to 10 shall be re-numbered as entries 2 to 9 respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (26954)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26954&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the Fourth`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, in the Table,—`
  line
  line `(a) entry 18 shall be re-numbered as entry 19 and before the entry as so re-numbered, the following`
  line `entry shall be inserted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"18. Himachal Pradesh......3";`
  line
  line `(b) entry 19 shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (26955)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Allocation of sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26955&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the three sitting members of the`
  line `Council of States representing the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh shall be deemed to have been duly`
  line `elected under clause (4) of article 80 to fill the three seats allotted to the State of Himachal Pradesh in that Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of such sitting membersshall remain unaltered.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (26956)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amendment of section 27A of Act 43 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26956&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in section 27A`
  line `of the Representation of the People Act, 1950, in sub-section (4), the words "Himachal Pradesh" shall be`
  line omitted.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (26957)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26957&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `[Allocation of seats in the existing House of the People.] Omitted by the State of Himachal,`
  line `Pradesh (Amendment) Act, 1971 (15 of 1971), s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-1-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (26958)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Provision as to sitting members.] Omitted by s.2, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-1-1971).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26958&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (26959)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Provision as to Legislative Assembly as constituted on the appointed day.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26959&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from`
  line `the appointed day, the total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from Assembly constituencies shall be sixty and the`
  line `number of seats to be reserved for the Scheduled Castes and for the Scheduled Tribes of that State`
  line `shall be fourteen and three respectively; and the Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act,`
  line `1950 (43 of 1950), shall be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the sixty territorial constituencies of the existing Union territory`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh shall be deemed to be the constituencies of the Legislative Assembly of the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh and the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1966, shall`
  line `be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the existing Union territory of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh representing a territorial constituency which, on the appointed day by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), becomes a constituency of the State of Himachal Pradesh, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `elected under article 170 to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh by that`
  line constituency.
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh shall be deemed to be duly constituted on the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (26960)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duration of Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26960&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The period of five years referred to in clause (1) of`
  line `article 172 shall, in the case of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh, be deemed to have`
  line `commenced on the day on which the duration of the existing Legislative Assembly of the Union territory`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh commenced under section 5 of the Government of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (26961)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Speaker and Deputy Speaker.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26961&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The persons who immediately before the appointed day .`
  line `are the`
  line `Speaker and the Deputy Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh shall be the Speaker and the Deputy Speaker, respectively, of the Legislative Assembly of the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh on and from that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (26962)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26962&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The rules of procedure and conduct of business of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh as in force immediately before the appointed`
  line `day shall, until rules are made under clause (1) of article 208, be the rules of procedure and conduct of business of`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh,subject to such modifications and adaptations as may`
  line `be made therein by the Speaker thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (26963)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Allocation of seats in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26963&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In the House of the People to be constituted`
  line `after the appointed day, there shall be allotted four seats to the State of Himachal Pradesh of which one seatshall`
  line `be reserved for the Scheduled Castes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (26964)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Allocation of seats in the Legislative Assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26964&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The total number of seats in the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh to be constituted at any time after the appointed day, to be filled by`
  line `persons chosen by direct election from territorial constituencies, shall be sixty-eight of which sixteen seatsshall be`
  line `reserved for the Scheduled Castes and three seatsshall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (26965)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Amendment of First and Second Schedules to Act 43 of 1950.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26965&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the Representation of the`
  line `People Act, 1950,`
  line
  line `(a) in the First Schedule,`
  line
  line `(i) under the heading "I. STATES", after entry 17, the following entry shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"18. Himachal Pradesh.....4 1.....";`
  line
  line `(ii) under the heading "II. UNION TERRITORIES", entry 6 relating to Himachal Pradesh shall`
  line `be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in the Second Schedule,--`
  line
  line `(i) under the heading "I. STATES", after entry 16, the following entry shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `"17. Himachal Pradesh.....68 16 3";`
  line
  line `(ii) under the heading "II. UNION TERRITORIES", entry 2 relating to Himachal Pradesh shall`
  line `be omitted.`
  line
  line `(2) The amendments made by clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1)shall have effect in relation to the House`
  line `of the People and the Legislative Assembly of Himachal Pradesh to be constituted at any time after the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (26966)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Delimitation of constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1971, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 5-1-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26966&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission shall, in the manner herein provided,`
  line `distribute, whether before or after the appointed day, the seats in the House of the People allotted to the State`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh under section 14 and the seats assigned to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh under section 15 to single-member territorial constituencies and delimit them on the basis of the latest`
  line `census figures, having regard to the provisions of the Constitution and to the following provisions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) all constituencies shall, as far as practicable, be geographically compact areas, and in delimiting`
  line `them regard shall be had to physical features, existing boundaries of administrative units, facilities of`
  line `communication and public convenience;`
  line
  line `(b) every assembly constituency shall be so delimited as to fall wholly within one parliamentary`
  line constituency;
  line
  line `(c) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Castes shall be distributed in`
  line `different parts of the State and located, as far as practicable, in those areas where the proportion of their`
  line `population to the total population is comparatively large; and`
  line
  line `(d) constituencies in which seats are reserved for the Scheduled Tribes shall, as far as practicable, be`
  line `located in areas where the proportion of their population to the total population is the largest.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, 'latest census figures" mean the census figures with respect to the existing`
  line `Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or, as the case may be, of the State of Himachal Pradesh ascertainable from`
  line `the latest census of which the finally published figures are available.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of assisting it in the performance of its functions under sub-section (1), the Election`
  line `Commission shall associate with itself as associate members,—`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) all the persons (or as many of them as are available) who having been elected from`
  line `parliamentary constituencies in the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, were members of the House`
  line `of the People immediately before its dissolution by the order of the President published with`
  line `notification No. 37/2/70/T, dated the 27th December, 1970, of the Lok Sabha Secretariat, in the`
  line `Gazette of India, dated the 27th December, 1970, or if the delimitation of any constituencies is taken`
  line `up after the first constitution, following such dissolution, of the House of the People, all the members`
  line `elected to such House (or as many of them as are available) from parliamentary constituencies in the`
  line `State of Himachal Pradesh; and]`
  line
  line `(b) such six of the members of the Legislative Assembly of the existing Union territory of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh or, as the case may be, of the State of Himachal Pradesh referred to in section 10 as the Speaker`
  line `thereof may nominate:`
  line
  line `Provided that none of the associate membersshall have a right to vote or to sign any decision of the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) If owing to death or resignation, the office of an associate member falls vacant, it shall be filled, if`
  line `practicable, in accordance with the provisions ofsub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The Election Commission shall—`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals for the delimitation of constituencies, together with the dissenting`
  line `proposals, if any, of any associate member who desires publication thereof, in the Official Gazette and in`
  line `such other manner as the Commission may consider fit, together with a notice inviting objections and`
  line `suggestions in relation to the proposals and specifying a date on or after which the proposals will be further`
  line `considered by it;`
  line
  line `(b) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the date so`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(c) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified, determine by one or more orders the delimitation of constituencies and cause such order`
  line `or orders to be published in the Official Gazette; and upon such publication, the order or ordersshall have the`
  line `full force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.`
  line
  line `(5) As soon as may be after such publication, every such order relating to parliamentary constituenciesshall be`
  line `laid before the House of the People and every such order relating to assembly constituenciesshall be laid before`
  line `the Legislative Assembly.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (26967)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Election Commission to maintain delimitation orders up-to-date.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26967&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election`
  line `Commission may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,—`
  line
  line `(a) correct any printing mistake in any order made under section 17 or any error arising therein from`
  line `inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any territorial division mentioned in any such order are or is`
  line `altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing such order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section relating to a parliamentary or an assembly constituency shall be laid,`
  line `as soon as may be after it is issued, before the House of the People or, as the case may be, the Legislative`
  line Assembly.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (26968)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Castes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26968&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Castes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Castes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951, shall stand amended as directed in the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (26969)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Amendment of Scheduled Tribes Orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26969&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution`
  line `(Scheduled Tribes) Order, 1950, shall stand amended as directed in the Third Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, the Constitution (Scheduled Tribes) (Union Territories) Order,`
  line `1951, shall stand amended as directed in the Fourth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (26970)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `High Court for Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26970&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be a`
  line `separate High Court for the State of Himachal Pradesh (hereinafter referred to as the High Court of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh).`
  line
  line `(2) The principal seat of the High Court of Himachal Pradesh shall be at Simla.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (26971)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Judges of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26971&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may, if he thinks fit, direct that such of the Judges of`
  line `the High Court of Delhi holding office immediately before the appointed day as may be determined by`
  line `him, shall on that day cease to be Judges of the High Court of Delhi and become Judges of the High Court`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons who by virtue of sub-section (1) becomes Judges of the High Court of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh shall, except in the case where any such person is appointed to be the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court, rank in that Court according to the priority of their respective appointments as Judges of the High`
  line `Court of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (26972)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Jurisdiction of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26972&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The High Court of Himachal Pradesh shall have, in respect of any`
  line `part of the territories comprised in the State of Himachal Pradesh, all such jurisdiction, powers and`
  line `authority as, under the law in force immediately before the appointed day, are exercisable in respect of`
  line `that part of the said territories by the High Court of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (26973)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Special provision relating to Advocates and Bar Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26973&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rule made or`
  line `direction given by the High Court of Himachal Pradesh in this behalf, any person who immediately before`
  line `the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Delhi shall be entitled to practise`
  line `as an advocate in the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) The right of audience in the High Court of Himachal Pradesh shall be regulated in accordance`
  line `with the like principles as immediately before the appointed day are in force with respect to the right of`
  line `audience in the High Court of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the appointed day, in the Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961) (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the Advocates Act), in section 3,—`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for clause (d), the following clauses shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“(d) for the States of Punjab and Haryana and the Union territory of Chandigarh, to be known`
  line `as the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana;`
  line
  line `(dd) for the State of Himachal Pradesh, to be known as the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(b) in clause (b) of sub-section (2), after the words “Bar Council of Orissa”, the words “, the Bar`
  line `Council of Himachal Pradesh” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of section 17 of the Advocates Act shall have effect in respect of the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Himachal Pradesh subject to the modifications that—`
  line
  line `(a) for clause (a) of sub-section (1) of the said section 17, the following clause shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `“(a) all persons who were entered as advocates on the roll of the Bar Council of Punjab and`
  line `Haryana immediately before the day appointed under clause (b) of section 2 of the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh Act, 1970, and who within three months from that day express in such manner`
  line `as the Bar Council of India may, by rules, prescribe an intention in writing to practise within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh”;`
  line
  line `(b) in clause (a) of sub-section (3) of the said section 17, for the words and figures “with his date`
  line `of enrolment under the Indian Bar Councils Act, 1926 (38 of 1926)”, the words “with his seniority on`
  line `the roll of the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Advocates Act as amended or modified by`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4),—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the first Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh under that Act, the fifteen members`
  line `required to be elected under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 3 of that Act, as amended by`
  line `sub-section (3), shall be nominated by the Chief Justice of the High Court of Himachal Pradesh from`
  line `amongst advocates who are entitled as of right to practise in the High Court of Himachal Pradesh and`
  line `are ordinarily practising within the territories comprised in the State of Himachal Pradesh and the`
  line `term of office of the members so nominated shall be one year from the date of the first meeting of the`
  line `Council or until their successors are duly elected in accordance with the provisions of the said Act,`
  line `whichever is earlier;`
  line
  line `(b) until the members of the first Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh required to be nominated`
  line `under clause (a) are duly nominated in accordance with the provisions of that clause, the Bar Council`
  line `of Punjab and Haryana shall function as the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh and the provisions of`
  line `the Advocates Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of persons entered on the roll of the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 17 of the Advocates Act, as`
  line `modified by sub-section (4), shall, as from the date or dates on which the names are so entered, stand`
  line `removed from the roll of the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana;`
  line
  line `(d) any proceedings which may be pending or which may be instituted against any person before`
  line `or by the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana immediately before his name is removed under clause`
  line `(c) from the roll of that Bar Council may after such removal be continued or instituted before or by`
  line `the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(e) every person who immediately before his name stands removed from the roll of the Bar`
  line `Council of Punjab and Haryana in accordance with the provisions of clause (c) is a member of the Bar`
  line `Council of Punjab and Haryana shall cease to be a member of that Council as from the date on which`
  line `his name stands so removed from the roll of that Bar Council;`
  line
  line `(f) the rules made or deemed to have been made by the Bar Council of Punjab and Haryana and in`
  line `force immediately before the date on which the first Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh is duly`
  line `constituted in accordance with the provisions of clause (a) shall, subject to such modifications and`
  line `adaptations as may be made therein by the Chairman of the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh, be`
  line `deemed to be rules made by the Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh and shall have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6) As soon as may be, after the first Bar Council of Himachal Pradesh is duly constituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (5), the assets and liabilities of the Bar`
  line `Council of Punjab and Haryana shall be apportioned between that Bar Council and the Bar Council of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh in such manner and proportion as may be agreed upon by the two Bar Councils and in`
  line `default of agreement with reference to any matter, the matter shall be referred to the Chairman of the Bar`
  line `Council of India and his decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Expressions used in this section but not defined in this Act shall have the meanings`
  line `assigned to them respectively in the Advocates Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (26974)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Practice and procedure in High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26974&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Part, the law in force`
  line `immediately before the appointed day with respect to practice and procedure in the High Court of Delhi`
  line `shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (26975)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Custody of seal of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26975&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with`
  line `respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Delhi shall, with the necessary modifications, apply`
  line `with respect to the custody of the seal of the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (26976)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Form of writs and other processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26976&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day`
  line `with respect to the form of writs and other processes used, issued or awarded by the High Court of Delhi`
  line `shall, with the necessary modifications, apply with respect to the form of writs and other processes used,`
  line `issued or awarded by the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (26977)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Powers of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26977&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the appointed day with respect to the`
  line `powers of the Chief Justice, single Judges and division courts of the High Court of Delhi and with respect`
  line `to all matters ancillary to the exercise of those powers shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in`
  line `relation to the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (26978)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Procedure as to appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26978&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The law in force immediately before the`
  line `appointed day relating to appeals to the Supreme Court from the High Court of Delhi and the Judges and`
  line `division courts thereof, shall, with the necessary modifications, apply in relation to the High Court of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (26979)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Transfer of proceedings from High Court of Delhi to High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26979&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided, the High Court of Delhi shall, on and from the appointed`
  line `day, have no jurisdiction in respect of the territories comprised in the State of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Delhi immediately before the appointed day as are`
  line `certified, whether before or after that day, by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the`
  line `place of accrual of the cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard`
  line `and decided by the High Court of Himachal Pradesh shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be`
  line `transferred to the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) of this section or in section 23, but`
  line `save as hereinafter provided, the High Court of Delhi shall have, and the High Court of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `shall not have, jurisdiction to entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the`
  line `Supreme Court, applications for review and other proceedings where any such proceedings seek any relief`
  line `in respect of any order passed by the High Court of Delhi before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after any such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court of Delhi, it`
  line `appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon`
  line `be transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Delhi—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day, in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Himachal`
  line `Pradesh by virtue of sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court Delhi retains jurisdiction by virtue of`
  line `sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect not only as an order of the High Court of Delhi, but also as an order`
  line `made by the High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in a court until that court has disposed of all issues`
  line `between the parties including any issues with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings`
  line `and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for`
  line `review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or division`
  line `court thereof, and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including`
  line `references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (26980)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Right to appear or to act in proceedings transferred to High Court of Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26980&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the appointed day, is an advocate entitled to practice in`
  line `the High Court of Delhi and was authorised to appear or to act in any proceedings transferred from that`
  line `High Court to the High Court of Himachal Pradesh under section 30 shall have the right to appear or to`
  line `act, as the case may be, in the High Court of Himachal Pradesh in relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (26981)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26981&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Part shall affect the application to the High Court of Himachal Pradesh`
  line `of any provisions of the Constitution, and this Part shall have effect subject to any provision that may be`
  line `made on or after the appointed day with respect to that High Court by any Legislature or other authority`
  line `having power to make such provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (26982)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Authorisation of expenditure pending its sanction by the Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26982&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may,`
  line `at any time before the appointed day, authorise by order such expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh as he deems necessary for a period of not more than six months beginning with the appointed`
  line `day, pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislative Assembly of the State of Himachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Governor of Himachal Pradesh may, after the appointed day, authorise by order such`
  line `further expenditure as he deems necessary from the Consolidated Fund of the State of Himachal Pradesh for any`
  line `period not extending beyond the said period of six months.`
  line
  line `(2) The President or, as the case may be, the Governor of Himachal Pradesh shall make separate orders`
  line `undersub-section (1) in respect of periods falling in different financial years.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (26983)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26983&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reports of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in section 49 of the`
  line `Government of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963), relating to the accounts of the existing Union territory`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be submitted to the Governor`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislative Assembly of the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor may, by order,—`
  line
  line `(a) declare any expenditure incurred out of the Consolidated Fund of the existing Union territory`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh on any service in respect of any period prior to the appointed day during the financial`
  line `year 1970-71 or in respect of any earlier financial year in excess of the amount granted for that service and for`
  line `that year as disclosed in the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to have been duly authorised, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for any action to be taken on any matter arising out of the said reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (26984)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Allowances and privileges of Governor of Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26984&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The allowances and privileges`
  line `of the Governor of Himachal Pradesh shall, until provision in that behalf is made by Parliament by law under`
  line `clause (3) of article 158, be such as the President may, by order, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (26985)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26985&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, by order, determine the grants-in-aid of the revenues`
  line `of the State of Himachal Pradesh and the share of that State in the Union duties of excise, estate duty and taxes on`
  line `income and for that purpose amend thereby the relevant provisions of the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution)`
  line `Act, 1962 (3 of 1962), the Additional Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the`
  line `Estate Duty (Distribution) Act, 1962 (9 of 1962), and the Constitution (Distribution of Revenues) Order, 1969`
  line `(C.O. 87), in such manner as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (26986)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Property, assets, rights, liabilities, obligations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26986&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) All such property and assets within the`
  line `existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh as are held immediately before the appointed day by the Union for purposes of governance of that Union territory shall, on and from that day, pass to the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh, unless the purposes for which such property and assets are so held are Union`
  line `purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cash balances in the treasuries in the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh before the`
  line `appointed day shall, as from that day, vest in the State of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligation (other than those relatable to, or in connection with, a Union`
  line `purpose), whether arising out of any contract or otherwise, which are, immediately before the appointed`
  line day,—
  line
  line `(a) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Central Government arising out of, or in`
  line `connection with, the governance of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh; or`
  line
  line `(b) the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Administrator of the existing Union territory of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh in his capacity as such, or of the Government of that Union territory,`
  line
  line `shall, on and from the appointed day, be the rights, liabilities and obligations of the Government of the`
  line `State of Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to recover arrears of—`
  line
  line `(a) any tax or duty being a tax or duty enumerated in the State List in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution, or`
  line
  line `(b) any duty referred to in article 268, or`
  line
  line `(c) any tax under the Central Sales Tax Act, 1956 (74 of 1956),`
  line
  line `which have fallen due in the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh shall pass to the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply to or in relation to,—`
  line
  line `(a) any benefit or burden of any assets, rights, liabilities or obligations of the Union under the`
  line `Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966 (31 of 1966) attributable to the transferred territories as defined in`
  line `the said Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any institution, undertaking or project the expenditure in relation to which is immediately`
  line `before the appointed day met from out of the Consolidated Fund of India;`
  line
  line `(c) any property which has been placed by the Union at the disposal of the Administration of the`
  line `existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh subject to the condition that the ownership thereof will`
  line `continue to vest in the Union.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) “liability” includes liability in respect of any civil deposit, local fund deposit, charitable or`
  line `other endowment, provident fund account, pension or actionable wrong;`
  line
  line `(b) “Union purposes” mean the purposes of Government relatable to any of the matters mentioned`
  line `in the Union List.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (26987)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Special provision as to transfer of assets, rights, liabilities, etc., of Union in relation to transferred territories under Act 31 of 1966.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26987&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression "successor States" and`
  line `"transferred territories" have the meaning respectively assigned to them in the Punjab Reorganisation Act,`
  line 1966.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order, transfer to the State of Himachal Pradesh the benefit or`
  line `burden of any assets rights, liabilities or obligations of the Union under the Punjab Reorganisation Act,`
  line `1966, in so far as such benefit or burden is, in the opinion of the Central Government, attributable to the`
  line `transferred territories.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made under sub-section (2) may provide that the State of Himachal Pradesh shall be`
  line `successor State in relation to the transferred territories for all or any of the purposes of the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966, or confer or impose on the State of Himachal Pradesh rights and obligations`
  line `which correspond so far as may be to the rights and obligations conferred or imposed on the successor`
  line `States by or under that Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 49, the Central Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `giving effect to the provisions of this section, by order, direct that the provisions of Part VI, Part VII, Part`
  line `VIII and Part IX and connected provisions of the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966, shall have effect`
  line `subject to such exceptions and modifications as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (26988)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Provisions relating to All-India Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26988&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, the expression "State cadre",—`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to the Indian Administrative Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian`
  line `Administrative Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to the Indian Police Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Police`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1954;`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to the Indian Forest Service, has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Forest`
  line `Service (Cadre) Rules, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the appointed day, there shall be constituted for the State of Himachal Pradesh a`
  line `State cadre of the Indian Administrative Service, a State cadre of the Indian Police Service and a State`
  line `cadre of the Indian Forest Service.`
  line
  line `(3) The initial strength and composition of each of the said State cadres shall be such as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(4) Such of the members of each of the said Services borne on the Union Territories cadre thereof`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, as the Central Government may, by order, specify, shall be`
  line `allocated to the State cadre of Himachal Pradesh of the same Service with effect from such date or dates`
  line `as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the operation after the appointed day of the`
  line `All-India Services Act 1951 (61 of 1951), or the rules or regulations made thereunder in relation to the`
  line `State cadres of the said Services referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) and in relation to the`
  line `members of those services borne on the State cadres.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (26989)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Provision relating to certain Services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26989&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `constituted for the State of Himachal Pradesh the following Services, namely:,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Himachal Pradesh Administrative Service; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Himachal Pradesh Police Service.`
  line
  line `(2) The initial strength and composition of the cadres of the said Services shall be such as the`
  line `Administrator of the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by order, determine before the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the appointed day, the existing Delhi, Himachal Pradesh and Andaman and Nicobar`
  line `Islands Civil Service (hereinafter referred to as the existing Civil Service) shall be known as the Delhi and`
  line `Andaman and Nicobar Islands Civil Service and Delhi, Himachal Pradesh and Andaman and Nicobar`
  line `Islands Police Service (hereinafter referred to as the existing Police Service) shall be known as the Delhi`
  line `and Andaman and Nicobar Islands Police Service.`
  line
  line `(4) Such members of the existing Civil Service as the Central Government may, by order, specify`
  line `shall be allocated to the cadre of the Himachal Pradesh Administrative Service and such members of the`
  line `existing Police Service as the Central Government may, by order, specify, shall be allocated to the cadre`
  line `of the Himachal Pradesh Police Service and any such order may specify the date or dates from which the`
  line `allocation made thereunder shall be effective.`
  line
  line `(5) All persons who are allocated under sub-section (4) and who immediately before the date on`
  line `which they are allocated, are borne on a Select List for promotion to a State cadre of an All-India Service,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been included in the same order as in that list in the Select List for promotion to`
  line `the State cadre of the same Service constituted under sub-section (2) of section 39.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section, the rules and regulations applicable to or in`
  line `relation to the members of the existing Civil Service and the existing Police Service as in force`
  line `immeditefy before the appointed day shall, so far as may, be apply respectively to and in relation to the`
  line `members of the Himachal Pradesh Administrative Service and the Himachal Pradesh Police Service, until`
  line `altered, repealed or amended by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(7) Every member of the Central Health Service who immediately before the appointed day is holding`
  line `any post in the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh being a post included in the authorised`
  line `strength of that Service, shall, until otherwise directed by the Central Government, be deemed to be on`
  line `deputation, on and from the appointed day, to the Government of the State of Himachal Pradesh on the`
  line `same terms and conditions of service as are applicable to him under the Central Health Service Rules,`
  line `1963, but without any deputation allowance:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of such deputation shall in no case extend beyond a period of three years`
  line `from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, "Central Health Service" means the Central Health Service`
  line `constituted under the Central Health Service Rules, 1963.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (26990)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Provisions relating to other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26990&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who immediately before the appointed`
  line `day is serving in connection with the affairs of the Union under the administrative control of the`
  line `Administrator of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh shall, unless otherwise directed by an order of`
  line `the Central Government, be deemed to have been allocated for service as from that day in connection with`
  line `the affairs of the State of Himachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that no directions shall be issued under this section after the expiry of a period of one year`
  line `from the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall affect the operation of section 82 of the Punjab`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1966 (31 of 1966).`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not apply in relation to persons to whom the provisions of`
  line `sections 39 and 40 apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (26991)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Other provisions as to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26991&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this section or sections 40 and 41 shall be`
  line `deemed to affect on or after the appointed day the operations of the provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of`
  line `the Constitution in relation to determination of the conditions of service of persons serving in connection`
  line `with the affairs of the State of Himachal Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day in the case of`
  line `any person referred to in section 40 or section 41 shall not be varied to his disadvantage except with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All services prior to the appointed day rendered by a person allocated under section 40 or deemed`
  line `to have been allocated under section 41 in connection with the administration of Union territory of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh, shall be deemed to have been rendered in connection with the affairs of the State of`
  line `Himachal Pradesh for the purposes of the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (26992)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Provisions as to continuance of officers in same posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26992&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Every person who immediately before`
  line `the appointed day is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in connection with the`
  line `administration of the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, shall continue to hold the same post or office`
  line `in the State of Himachal Pradesh and shall be deemed, on and from that day, to have been duly appointed`
  line `to the post or office by the Government of, or other appropriate authority in, the State of Himachal`
  line Pradesh;
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a competent authority on or after the`
  line `appointed day from passing in relation to such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (26993)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26993&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order establish one or more advisory`
  line `committees for the purpose of assisting it in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) the discharge of its functions under this Part; and`
  line
  line `(b) the ensuring of fair and equitable treatment to all persons affected by the provisions of this`
  line `Part and the proper consideration of any representations made by such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (26994)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26994&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to the Government of the State of Himachal Pradesh as may appear to it to be necessary for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the foregoing provisions of this Part and also the provisions of Part IX of the`
  line `Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966 (31 of 1966), and the State Government shall comply with such`
  line directions.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (26995)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Amendment of article 210 and article 239A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26995&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day—`
  line
  line `(a) in article 210, in clause (2), the following proviso shall be inserted at the end, namely;—`
  line
  line `"Provided that in relation to the Legislature of the State of Himachal Pradesh this clause shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words "fifteen years" occurring therein, the words "twenty-five years"`
  line `were substituted.";`
  line
  line `(b) in article 239A, in clause (1), the words "Himachal Pradesh" shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (26996)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Amendment of Act 37 of 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26996&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in clause (a) of section 15 of`
  line `the States Reorganisation Act, 1956,—`
  line
  line `(i) for the word "Punjab", the words "Punjab, Himachal Pradesh"`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words "Himachal Pradesh and Chandigarh", the words "and Chandigarh" shall be`
  line substituted.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (26997)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Amendment of Act 20 of 1963.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26997&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, in the Government of Union`
  line `Territories Act, 1963, in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 2 and in sub-section (2) of section 44, the`
  line `words "Himachal Pradesh" shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (26998)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Continuance of existing laws and their adaptation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26998&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) All laws in force, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, in the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh shall continue to be in force in the`
  line `State of Himachal Pradesh until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of facilitating the application in relation to the State of Himachal Pradesh of any`
  line `law made before the appointed day, the appropriate Government may, within two years from that day, by`
  line `order, make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or amendment, as`
  line `may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to the adaptations`
  line `and modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent Legislature or other`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means, as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, the Central`
  line `Government; and as respects any other law, the Government of the State of Himachal Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (26999)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=26999&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made under section 49 for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or`
  line `authority required or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in`
  line `relation to the State of Himachal Pradesh, construe the law in such manner not affecting the substance as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (27000)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Provisions as to continuance of courts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=27000&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `All courts and tribunals and all authorities`
  line `discharging lawful functions throughout the existing Union territory of Himachal Pradesh or any part`
  line `thereof immediately before the appointed day shall, unless their continuance is inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or until other provision is made by a competent Legislature or other competent`
  line `authority, continue to exercise their respective functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (27001)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Effect of provisions of Act inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=27001&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (27002)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=27002&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the President may, by order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to`
  line `him to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (27003)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961&sectionId=27003&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00004_197053_1517807317961
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before such`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the sessions in`
  line `which it is so laid or the session immediately following" (w.e.f. 5-5-1986).`
